reviews.text: This is one of if not the best outdoor space in Fremont. Lake Elizabeth is a nice size (for a city) lake with fishing, paddle boats, and bird watching. The paved path around the lake is nice for strolling, jogging, biking, etc. There is an Aqua Park inside this park with lots of water slides. Great play equipment all throughout...Recommended..

Visited and thoroughly enjoyed 4.7km walk around lake. Largely a shaded track, it would be difficult for the mobility impaired. The lake is white scenic and an excellent opportunity to leave the crowds on the surf coast for a closer encounter with nature! There are bench seats to rest on and admire the view. We did the lap in just over an hour and then then wonderful lunch in nearby Forrest. You could easily take a picnic and spend longer. The circuit can be done clockwise, starting just short of the canoe launching platform on the left, or keep to the right of the lake viewing platforms and travel anti clockwise. (The signage is lacking at this point.)
A picnic ground is close to the car park. Toilets are also available.There is also a separate camping ground, though only suitable for tents as cars a parked a little distance away. It is not suitable for caravans or camping trailers.
Beautiful place! Love to take the kid's to the park and to get a good walk there.

The park is great, just one suggestion, and please consider what I say. I humbly request that you add an outdoor archery range, as the closest one is about 50 minutes drive away. There is a considerable and growing population of archers in this area. Even a really small archery range would be good. A fee is fine, but I think that such a place would really draw new crowds of youth and elderly alike to have some fun in the sun. 
Please like this comment so that the city will see it
Thank you
I would definitely reccomend it!

The original Spanish mission was erected in 1797. Most of what you can see now has been carefully and painstakingly rebuilt and touched up through generous donations.
I haven’t seen all of the Spanish missions in California, but this one strikes me as pretty simple and practical. 
As for whether the Spanish colonial legacy around the world is something to celebrate (any colonial legacy for that matter) is up to you, but at the end of the day it’s a physical part of history that doesn’t let us forget.
One time visit typically good for people who love history
Cool spot to take in some California history!
If you have been one Mission you have seen them all.

Gift shop had a nice selection of items. Staff was friendly and knowledgeable. Church was very beautiful and museum was full of the mission history and purpose. Added bonus, my kiddos were "creeped out" by the cemetery!

Small and cozy place with approx 60 seating capacity. Has a good structure to it. The actor talent is excellent. During the 15 min break of the play, they offer tea/coffee with light snacks. They should do such showes more often.

A delightful little theater 
Unfortunately it is closing.
Always fun and the cost is very reasonable.
Great place. I've been to two plays here. Very nice staff and actors. Small vintage theater with warm cozy feel.
Their plays are really top notch and so well staged for such a small theatre.

This is another of Fremont’s gems. If you’re a fan of silent films or enjoy movie history, this a must see. The museum is modest but very interesting and continues to grow funded by donors. And every Saturday night and Sunday afternoon (mostly) silent films are shown in the old theater that has been fixed up to look as it did when Charlie Chaplin and Bronco Billy Anderson made films in the Niles area. One of the most interesting parts of the theater is its original projection room that had been sealed up for decades when the theater was sold with its original projection equipment in place.

Interesting stop on our visit to Niles. Our docent was very knowledgeable and it was a nice tour. I'd like to go back and enjoy a movie! It's tiny and the gift shop is bigger than the museum itself. Worth a look!

A great experience!  Brought the family here.  Fun way to learn history and have a wonderful time.  First time people get to go into the projection room which was sealed for 80 years.  We will be going again.

I have been living in and around Niles all of my life. 
I was walking through Niles with a friend from out of town and we walked into the Museum.  I believe our tour guide had mentioned the Museum had opened in 2012.
I had been living away from my hometown for several years.
Was really nice to discover this Museum, the tour guide was knowledgable, and friendly.
I learned a few things that I didn't already know, saw the theater that featured silent movies, saw the projection room full of old reels, and antique equipment.
My friend was very impressed to learn that nearby Niles Canyon was frequently used as a backdrop for some of the movies for Bronco Billy and Charlie Chaplin.
There were framed photographs on the walls of the bungalows that housed the casts and crews in the alleys behind the buildings on the main street, also a souvenir shop.
We very much enjoyed the display of antique clothing worn for that period.
No fee to enter or tour, however, a donation jar is on the counter if you wish to support their efforts.
Large parking lot across the street for free parking.
Enjoy!

If you enjoy local history, the Museum is a treasure trove of local history....and it's connection to the film industry. They also show Silent Movies every Saturday night. The piano accompianist is remarkable, playing background music for the movie with no sheet music and playing non stop for the length of the show. Amazing!! Now that's Talent. The evening we attended the movies, there were quite a few school aged children in the audience. I thought they would be bored because they were used to all the modern movie technology, but to my surprise, they we're loving it all. Some school classes go there as a field trip and make their own videos at the location spots they had seen in the movies. There is a walking tour of all the historic locations. A definite Must Visit!

We had our wedding reception here, prices per table were fair. They were flexible and accommodating with the services. A lot of parking. The dance floor was a little small. Everyone had fun, so it was worth it.
good food but the price is high per dish
Some of the service people only speak Cantonese and expect customers to understand
Taste is great! Ordered duck , lamb, fried shrimp with pumkin, tofu, 卤水拼盘, soup.
Nice place and decent food
Great service. Good meats. Decent selection of hotpot thingiemajiggs. All in all great value. Would recommend.
Love that they have 4 choices of soup base. There are a lot of meat and veggie choices. Service is good. Recommend for dinner with a small group of people.

Food was good but mandatory 18% tip added to bill with the audacity to ask for additional tips on the credit card receipt. If tip is mandatory it should be stated somewhere rather than a surprise addition at the end.

Went here with some coworkers while visiting the US. Prices here are comparable to Canada after the currency exchange. The food was plentiful and good. We had the the miso, pork and spicy broth. The pork broth was good, and became more flavourful as various meats were cooked in it. Miso broth was okay. The spicy broth was too spicy for me, so I avoided it.

There is an AYCD option as well, however, everyone at the table would need to buy into that.

Very fast service for an AYCE restaurant as well as short wait to get seated. Overall headed to this place since Little Dipper Shabu was super packed (my go to). Overall the mushroom soup base is pretty good, aside from that, the soup bases were lackluster and didn't have much flavor depth to them. Not bad selection of meat. I see they're unique with trying 4 bases... But quality>quantity at the end of the day. The sauce bar was badly organized and just in an awkward place. Also wished their Chinese donuts were crispy and not cold and soft.

The food quality is very good. Quantity of food is also quite good compared to price. I could not finish one dish, it is that good quantity. This place has good variety of afghan cuisine. I tried rice with chicken and it was delicious. Lamb dishes are also good.

The place is little cozy and often crowded. So if you go in peak lunch time, you may have to wait. There is parking in next block and you generally will find a spot there. It is good place overall for team lunch on friday.

The ambience is so so, but the food is top notch. They've definitely got their own signature flavors, especially when it comes to the meats. The staff is courteous and responsive. If you go on a Saturday or Sunday evening expect a long wait time but other that they deserve high marks for the quality of food you get. I hope the same management stays and the same kitchen staff too.

Fun restaurant with great food and warm cozy ambiance. Just come prepared to wait, as they don't take reservations and also have a very busy take out business that is competing for the staff's attention. But definitely yummy food.
The best kabobs in Fremont!! I been coming here for years. Nice people great food.
Delicious and authentic a Afghanistan food. At reasonable price. The front door of the restaurant is a 300 plus years old Afghanistan!

I used to love E-bar. Recently, they changed their food/cooks and it took a downgrade. The chicken strips taste like plastic/cartilage and many other items taste different. I used to religiously love eating the chicken strips but I’m sad it’s not the same.
I always love coming here. The food is great and so is the service. A good variety of foods and drinks.

Great looking place, as they all are but how they have fallen. The food, barely edible, it had obviously been microwaved. I don’t think there is a single thing that is prepared on site. 

The mixed drinks are also all from a can, no real bar tender skill there either. 

Enjoy!

I love elephant bar (for reasons I can't fully explain). This is one of the last few locations left. I sit around the bar with my wife, have a couple drinks, eat a few random sides, and a good time is had by all.

Our server Jennifer was great! The light chicken lettuce wraps were good. The chicken tacos were decent. My friends spinach dip was cold and her potatoes skins were burnt. I've been to this location a few times and its never very busy.

Service wasn't bad for Chinese food, and the dim sum was great! I thought the price wasn't bad at all for a white-tablecloth dim sum place. I would definitely be happy to go back! Good assortment of the usual dim sum items, along with more traditional dishes.

Incredible Cantonese seafood restaurant! The restaurant is famous for live high quality seafood. The crab was from Australia, and was done two ways, fried and steamed. Both were delicious and sweet, especially the steamed legs with green bean noodles beneath absorbing the juice. The prawns were big and sweet, and the garlic bean shoots fresh. The turtle jelly dessert was good.
Credit accepted, free parking lot, can be very expensive

If I can give this place 0 stars I would, the staff was rude and even threw the bowls at our table, we order a lot of dishes and the rice came right in the end. We asked him nicely and he not only screams at us and still takes till the end when we about to finish and then like I mentioned in the beginning, threw the bowls at the table. Never come to the place, food was not even that good. Would not recommend to anyone. Just don't come here.
Average dim sum. Very high price. Nice setting. But not for choosie with high expectation on taste for the price they charge.
A Chinese seafood restaurant offering speciality seafood items like crab from Australia, live fishes, etc.  service is fine.
Amazing food!!
Nice place. They Always service very good and fresh food. I got a soup and liked it so much. Their prices are also on affordable range.

Been here first time to try when i heart they have new management, it was good choice to come, we ordered 3 meals, and all good for u guys can come to try, mine was Bun Bo Hue broth was good but not spicy so everyone can eat, my husband was pad Thai and my mom was pho
The best pho I have ever been. Good service and they make pho very fast. I love it.
Good service, constantly going our table asking if we need anything and if everything is good
It’s nice restaurant, I really like this food and will come back soon ! ❤️

Food is good here. Red/green/yellow curries are good. Fried rice is also good but gets heavy. Place is big but still crowded in peak lunch time. Ambience is good and wait time to get served is longer than typical. Parking nearby is ample.

The food is high quality and very delicious. My friend and I go there when ever we have a craving for Thai food. My favorite dish is Pad See Yu. It's thinly sliced beef with broccoli and wide noodles in a scrumptious sauce. You have the option of ordering it spicy or mild. The Thai iced tea is delicious! The restaurant is always full but the wait is not very long. The staff is friendly and helpful if you have questions. They do a tremendous business, it's always busy. Best time to go is around 5:00 if you enjoy an earlier dinner. If you have to wait, it's well worth it!

Looked like a busy place even on a weeknight. However service was pretty good. They were quick to take the ordered and didn't have to wait more than 10 minutes for food to be brought to the table. The appetizer and the main course brought together.

We had the Angel Chicken Wings for starters. This was pretty good. The best amongst everything else I had.

We then had the Basil Fried Rice with chicken and Shrimp and my friend had the Fried Rice with Fried Chicken. Both these dishes were okay. I love Thai food and have had the same dish in many places. So comparatively it was just okay. I felt there was too much oil used which was masking all the other flavors.

We wanted to order one of the Curry's on the menu. But they said we have to order rice separately for that. That was a bit weird.

So:
Service: 5
Food: 3.5
Price: 3.5
Value for money: 3

There are many more items on the menu to choose from. So the 3.5 average rating I have given doesn't mean I am disappointed but it just  goes for the dishes I tried today.

Great place to grab Thai food. The Pad Thai was phenomenal and the noodle texture perfect. The fried fish was also to die for. The only negative is the smaller portions but overall, the food was really good.
Busy during evenings. Ideal for small and large groups. Kind staff, quick service, delicious food. Vegetarians have good options too. The soups served here are amazing! Do check them out!

Delicious food and excellent service! Tonight was our first experience eating Indian cuisine. Our waiter was knowledgeable and friendly with his recommendations and my husband and I both truly enjoyed our experiences.  We would recommend this restaurant to friends and family, and we will definitely be coming back ourselves.
This place was great. We ordered Lamb chops and chicken masala? (The first menu in curry categories) and they were nice. We will visit there again definitely.
The food is amazing and the wait staff so friendly. Every time we are in Ann Arbor we eat there as no other Indian restaurant is as good. We've been eating there for 20 years.

One of the best Indian restaurants I've eaten at and I have been eating there for years. Reminds me of the nicer Indian restaurants in Great Brittan where I first tried Indian food. Authentic food served in a very nice atmosphere. The waiters are all very professional and efficient. I asked about a dish I used to order but was not on the menu now and the waiter said they would make it for me... Chicken Hyderabadi (not sure I spelled that right) delicious! I'll back when I'm in town again.

The food is delicious in every word possible! I went with my mom, and she's usually picky when it comes to food, but she absolutely loved their food. Our waiter was the best! The prices are not that bad. The service was good, a man in a suit (I believe the owner) came to our to check up on us. All in all, it was a great first experience.
This is heaven thick meat tender flavorful can't get enough of it
Once I know that this place is really great.

I've been here quite a few times with my parents. These are the dishes I've had here:
- green onion and pork dry noodle: It was really oily, but the flavor was really good and unique. There was a lot of meat, and I wish they put vegetables or something because I sort of got tired of eating it after a while. It could also do with more onion!
- pork noodle soup: The fried pork pieces were too thin and too dry, so the pork wasn't too good. The noodles were good too. The soup had a bone base, so the soup itself has flavor. The noodle soup and noodles were really good, pork not so much.
- watercress wonton soup: I really like the dumpling skin. It's quite chewy and sturdy, unlike a lot of skins which are really soft and somewhat mushy. The insides are good too; vegetable dumplings are so good. The soup it got served in is good too; again, the soup has a bone base, so the soup has flavor. They also put egg strips and seaweed too. Yum! The only complaint I have is the soup was more oily than it could have been.
- spicy beef noodle soup: beef is really tender, and there are green vegetables (yay)! There are a lot of noodles, and it's sufficiently spicy. Quite good.
- Shanghai soup dumplings (xiao long bao): they're decent! There's soup inside, and the skin is pretty chewy and good. There's a lot of meat inside, and it's pretty tender. I was pretty impressed with these.
- vegetable with rice cake: it was too salty and oily, but the flavor was pretty good. The portions were small compared to the other portions they serve, but still decent.

All the dishes had really huge portions! And for so cheap. They also give free tea eggs, one for each dish you order I think. Quite good. I would definitely come here again if I want to eat noodles.
Clean, quiet and fast. The rice is outstanding ! I had beef noodles w green onion;  the green onions were a lil charred and that's how I love them.

Second time to this restaurant, basically ok....
But, too oily, maybe is Shanghai style....
Sesame noodle is too sweet and not so hot, better to remind them.

Made reservation for the dinner, but still waited in the door for 10+ minutes, not because it's crowded ( I can see the seats were reserved). After we finally set in the table, we had another 20+ minutes wait for the order, no body seems care about us, so we left. I felt the restaurant was treating us as the beggars to beg their food. Eating in a restaurant suppose to be a happy time, but instead being treated badly, and suffered a lot of disappointments.
A hidden gem in residential Fremont.  Love the grilled Saba. Simple can be Devine.

I had been here so many years and so many times. The food is good and the price is ok. After old owner, waiters, and waitresses left and no longer work there except one waitress remaining she is good waitress. Not long ago they hired a new waitress she is so mean and rude and unhappy person. Whenever the time for it to be closed and customer still eating at their table she is making loud noise, start banding the table, vacuum, pushing customer to get out. I don't think she is a right person for the job. I think that is one of the reason they're been losen customer a lot not because their food.
Order from the daily specials menu. Those are the best! But they run out quickly.

probably best Japanese in Fremont
The daily specials is always a treat and the fish is high quality. Nov 2018 update: lost sushi chef, sushi bar closed. a few walked out because of that
